	<tr>
		<td valign=middle align=left width=22><IMG src="/help/images/clear.gif" height=1 width=20 border=0></td>
		
    <td valign=middle align=right class="header">Activating The Intranet Account</td>
	</tr>
	<tr><td valign=top align=left colspan="2"><hr size="1"></td></tr>
	<tr>
    <td valign=top align=left colspan="2" class="text">In order to use the messaging 
      module to send any intranet message to a EKP user, an Intranet account has 
      to be activated. The activation is done only once.</td>
  </tr>
	<tr><td valign=top align=left colspan="2" class="text"><IMG src="/help/images/clear.gif" height=5 width=1 border=0></td></tr>
    <tr>
		<td valign=top align=left width=22 class="text">1.</td>
		
    <td valign=top align=left class="text">Click on the <strong>Messaging</strong> 
      link from the main menu.</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td valign=top align=left width=22><span class="text">2.</span></td>
		<td valign=top align=left class="text">
			Fill up the following fields:<br><br>
			<li>Internet Email Address - User's email address</li>
			
      <li>Indicator Colour - Choose any colour to indicate that it is an intranet 
        message in the Inbox</li>
			<li>SMTP Server Name - SMTP server name or IP adrress</li>
			<li>SMTP Port - Default port 25</li>
			<li>Authenticated SMTP Server - Default</li>
			
      <li>SMTP Username - User's email address</li>
			<li>Signature - Email signature</li>
		</td>
	</tr>
</table>
